        <presentation>&lt;p&gt;Consider any situation where a person throws a ball upward, as shown.  Suppose the &lt;strong&gt;system is the ball and the Earth&lt;/strong&gt;.  Since  the ball's height changes, and the Earth is included, the system's gravitational potential energy, \( U_G \) is changing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/person_throw_ball_up.png" alt="Person throwing a ball upward" width="350" height="149" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Where is \( U_G = 0 \)?&lt;/p&gt;</presentation>
